    "---\n",
    "## 4 — Dask (distributed / thread pool)\n",
    "Split the N particles into chunks. Each chunk computes forces for its own particles\n",
    "using the full position array. Chunks run in parallel via `dask.delayed`.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key overhead:** task scheduling (~0.5–1ms per task) + barrier at each timestep.\n",
    "Dask wins when N is large or when you have a real cluster — not for N < 500 on one node."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "import dask\n\ndef _chunk_forces(pos_chunk, pos_all):\n    diff      = pos_all[np.newaxis,:,:] - pos_chunk[:,np.newaxis,:]  # (k,N,3)\n    dist2     = np.sum(diff**2, axis=2) + EPS**2\n    inv_dist3 = dist2**(-1.5)\n    return G*M**2 * np.sum(diff * inv_dist3[:,:,np.newaxis], axis=1)\n\ndef forces_dask(pos, n_chunks=4):\n    chunks    = np.array_split(pos, n_chunks, axis=0)\n    delayed_f = [dask.delayed(_chunk_forces)(c, pos) for c in chunks]\n    return np.vstack(dask.compute(*delayed_f, scheduler='threads'))\n\ndef step_dask(pos, vel, n_chunks=4):\n    F = forces_dask(pos, n_chunks)\n    vel += F / M * DT\n    pos += vel * DT\n    return pos, vel\n\ncheck('dask', forces_dask(pos_t, n_chunks=4), F_ref)"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 5a — CuPy (GPU vectorized)\n",
    "Identical idiom to `forces_vectorized` — just swap `np` → `cp`.\n",
    "CuPy dispatches the broadcast as a fused CUDA kernel automatically.\n",
    "Data must live on the GPU (`cp.array`). H→D copy happens once before the time loop."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import cupy as cp\n",
    "\n",
    "def forces_cupy(pos_cp):\n",
    "    diff      = pos_cp[cp.newaxis,:,:] - pos_cp[:,cp.newaxis,:]  # on GPU\n",
    "    dist2     = cp.sum(diff**2, axis=2) + EPS**2\n",
    "    inv_dist3 = dist2**(-1.5)\n",
    "    return G*M**2 * cp.sum(diff * inv_dist3[:,:,cp.newaxis], axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "def step_cupy(pos_cp, vel_cp):\n",
    "    F       = forces_cupy(pos_cp)\n",
    "    vel_cp += F / M * DT\n",
    "    pos_cp += vel_cp * DT\n",
    "    return pos_cp, vel_cp\n",
    "\n",
    "pos_cp = cp.array(pos_t)\n",
    "F_cp   = forces_cupy(pos_cp)\n",
    "check('cupy', cp.asnumpy(F_cp), F_ref)"
   ]
  },
